{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"431","heading":"Application of chapter 71 of title 5, relating to Federal service labor-management relations; procedures for remedy of violations","label":"431 Application of chapter 71 of title 5, relating to Federal service labor-management relations; procedures for remedy of violations","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/ch5/schII/ptD","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSubsecs. (c) and (d) of this section effective , see .Oct. 26, 1996section 471(b) of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Labor-Management Rights","label":"a .—Labor-Management Rights","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Subject to subsection (d), chapter 71 of title 5 shall apply to employing offices and to covered employees and representatives of those employees, except that covered employees shall not have a right to reinstatement pursuant to section 7118(a)(7)(C) or 7123 of title 5.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Definition","label":"b .—Definition","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For purposes of the application under this section of chapter 71 of title 5, the term “agency” as used in such chapter means an employing office.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Regulations To Implement Section.—","label":"c Regulations To Implement Section.—","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":".—In general","label":"1 .—In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Federal Labor Relations Authority shall issue regulations to implement this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":".—Agency regulations","label":"2 .—Agency regulations","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to the extent the Authority may determine, for good cause shown and stated together with the regulation, that a modification of such regulations would be more effective for the implementation of the rights and protections under this section; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"as the Authority may determine that a modification of such regulations is necessary to avoid a conflict of interest or appearance of a conflict of interest.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Specific Regulations Regarding Applications to Certain Employing Offices.—","label":"d Specific Regulations Regarding Applications to Certain Employing Offices.—","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":".—Regulations required","label":"1 .—Regulations required","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/d/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fd%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to the extent the Authority may determine, for good cause shown and stated together with the regulation, that a modification of such regulations would be more effective for the implementation of the rights and protections under this section; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/d/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t3/s431/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft3%2Fs431%2Fd%2F1%